        id: 'd5s1',
        title: 'The Bruise on Monday Morning',
        situation: 'On Monday morning, a teacher notices that 5-year-old Jaylen has a large bruise on his upper arm and a smaller one on his neck. When asked what happened, Jaylen says "Daddy got really mad." The teacher comes to you immediately. The father, who dropped Jaylen off, is still in the parking lot.',
        question: 'What do you do in the next 10 minutes?',
        discussion: 'You are a mandated reporter and this situation meets the threshold for reasonable suspicion of physical abuse. You must report to DFPS immediately — call 1-800-252-5400 right now. Do not confront the father in the parking lot. Do not investigate yourself. Do not wait to "see if there are more signs." Do not call the parent to ask about the bruise before reporting. Your job is to report, not to investigate. While you or the teacher makes the report, ensure Jaylen is safe and supervised inside the building. Document everything: what was observed, what Jaylen said, the exact words he used, the time, and who was present. Notify your director. DFPS will take it from there. The father being in the parking lot does not change your obligation — if you are concerned about immediate safety, you can ask DFPS for guidance on whether to detain the child.',
